A batch job is a process that runs on the server in the background instead of running immediately in the user session. 
It is useful for long-running or repetitive work, such as generating reports, updating records in bulk, sending integration data, or cleaning old logs. 
Batch jobs can run once, run on a schedule, and be monitored from the Batch jobs pages.

when do we use the batch jobs 
>> the process takes time
>> many records must be processed
>> the user should not wait on the form
>> the process must run daily/hourly/weekly
>> the job should run at night or off-hours
>> the work should be retried or monitored centrally.

